You have exceeded your premium request allowance. We have automatically switched you to GPT-4.1 which is included with your plan. [Enable additional paid premium requests](command:chat.enablePremiumOverages) to continue using premium models.```seqdiag
actor User
boundary ProductPage
participant ":ProductRoute" as ProductRoute
control AuthMiddleware
control ProductController
participant ":ProductService" as ProductService
participant ":ProductModel" as ProductModel
database Database

User->ProductPage: 1. Click "Delete" on a product
activate ProductPage
activate User
ProductPage-->User: 2. Show confirmation dialog
User->ProductPage: 3. Confirm delete

ProductPage->ProductRoute: 4. DELETE /products/{id}
activate ProductRoute

ProductRoute->AuthMiddleware: 5. AuthenticateUser(req, res, next)
activate AuthMiddleware
#ref over User, Database: Verifies token
AuthMiddleware->ProductController: 6. Forward DeleteProductRequest(productId)
deactivate AuthMiddleware
activate ProductController

ProductController->ProductService: 7. Process product deletion
activate ProductService

alt Product not found
    ProductService->ProductModel: 8.1. Find product by ID
    activate ProductModel

    ProductModel->Database: 8.1.1. Retrieve product data by ID
    activate Database
    Database-->ProductModel: 8.1.2. Result (null)
    deactivate Database

    ProductModel-->ProductService: 8.1.3. Return not found
    deactivate ProductModel

    ProductService-->ProductController: 8.1.4. Return not found result
    ProductController-->ProductRoute: 8.1.5. Return 404 Not Found + message
    ProductRoute-->ProductPage: 8.1.6. Show error: "Product not found"
        ProductPage--> User: 8.1.6. Show error: "Product not found"

else Product exists
    ProductService->ProductModel: 8.2. Delete product by ID
    activate ProductModel

    ProductModel->Database: 8.2.1. Persist deletion
    activate Database
    Database-->ProductModel: 8.2.2. Delete success
    deactivate Database

    ProductModel-->ProductService: 8.2.3. Return deletion result
    deactivate ProductModel

    ProductService-->ProductController: 8.2.4. Return DeleteProductResponse
    deactivate ProductService
    ProductController-->ProductRoute: 8.2.5. Return 200 OK + success message
    deactivate ProductController
    ProductRoute-->ProductPage: 8.2.6. Show delete success
        ProductPage--> User: 8.2.6. Show delete success

    deactivate ProductRoute
end

deactivate ProductPage
deactivate User
```